    "en": {
      "title": "Historic Appropriation Bill to Parliament",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "For the first time in the history of Sri Lanka, President Ranil Wickramasinghe, as the Minister of Finance, is going to submit the Appropriation Bill to the Parliament tomorrow (30th), which has exceeded the state expenditure of 4 trillion.",
        "According to this appropriation bill, the state expenditure has been increased to 4672 billion rupees.",
        "The total cost of the Appropriation Bill to be presented tomorrow is recorded as 2249 billion in recurrent costs, 1334 billion in interest costs, and 1809 billion in capital costs.",
        "The revised budget that will be presented to Parliament tomorrow has increased the amount of 773 billion rupees over the approved budget of 2022."
      ],
